page.title: 02ECOLOGY
page.content: THE RIVER & A NUMBER OF INLAND LAKES & PONDS PROVIDE FISHING.THE LAKE AT FENN FARM FOR INSTANCE IS STOCKED WITH TROUT. THERE ARE SOME GOOD BUT LITTLE USED FOOTPATHS.QUITE A LOT OF HEDGES & TREES REMAIN.PHEASANTS & WILD LIFE STILL FIND AREAS OF COVER.RABBITS & PIGEONS ARE A PROBLEM FOR FARMERS & GARDENERS.MOORHENS WERE CITED AS A PEST BY ONE FARMER.FROGS ARE RARE BUT KESTRELS & MAGPIES HAVE MADE A COMEBACK.ROE DEER & BADGER HAVE BEEN SEEN ON THE SCHOOL FIELD.TAMARIND AT BULMER SCHOOL SUMS IT UP"IT IS A PLEASANT AREA,PEACEFUL & PEOPLE COME FROM TOWNS LIKE LONDON TO GET AWAY FROM ROARING TRAFFIC.IT HAS A NICE SELECTION OF WALKS & PONY PATHS." MOTORISTS BEWARE OF NARROW LANES.
